@graph.name: Data-specific substitution models improve protein-based phylogenetics
@graph.description: Data sets, data-specific amino-acid substitution models, and optimal ML trees.

@graph.name: Centro de Ciências do Mar do Algarve
1_simulated_data_sets
@graph.description: Simulated sequence alignments generated with 400, 1500, and 8000 sites, with 100 replicates for each length.

@graph.name: 2_simulated_data_specific_models
@graph.description: Data-specific amino-acid substitution models estimated from the simulated sequence alignments with 400, 1500, and 8000 sites

@graph.name: 3_optimal_ML_trees_simulated_data
@graph.description: Optimal ML trees inferred in IQ-TREE (vers. 1.6.8) using data-specific models, the gcpREV model (simulation model), and the commonly-used empirical models cpREV and WAG.

@graph.name: 4_data_specific_models_empirical_data
@graph.description: Data-specific amino-acid substitution models estimated from the published data sets, namely, Timme et al., 2012; Zeng et al., 2014; Leliaert et al., 2016; Feuda et al., 2017; Munro et al., 2018; Schulz et al., 2018; Schwentner et al., 2017 (Matrix 1); Toussaint et al., 2018 (DT369); Irisarri et al., 2020; and Koenen et al., 2020.

@graph.name: 5_optimal_ML_trees_empirical_data
@graph.description: Optimal ML trees inferred from the published data sets using the data-specific models with the same among-rate site variation parameters as used in the original studies.

@graph.name: AminoacidsModelFormatConvertor.py
@graph.description: Convert MCMC parameters (inferred using the P4 package (Foster,2004)), paml, and RAxML model formats to paml, RAxML or Phylobayes model formats.

@graph.name: SimulateSequenceData.py
@graph.description: Alignment data simulator. It generates several data sets in phylip format using a given model and tree.

@graph.name: TreeDistanceCalculator.py
@graph.description: Check several trees (in the working folder) against a simulation tree. For equal topologies, it also outputs weighted Robinson-Foulds and Felsenstein branch length distances.

@graph.name: calculate_model_parameters_ML_P4.py
@graph.description: Calculate model parameters by ML optimisation.
